    </li>
  </ul>

  <!-- Martial Arts Descriptions -->

  <div class="martial-section">
    <h3>Karate (Striking Arts)</h3>
    <p>Karate is a traditional martial art originating from Okinawa, Japan. It developed from indigenous fighting methods combined with Chinese martial arts, forming a system focused on striking techniques.</p>
    <p>The art emphasizes punches, kicks, knee strikes, and open-hand techniques. Practitioners learn forms (kata), basic drills (kihon), and sparring (kumite) to develop power and control.</p>
    <p>Karate promotes discipline, respect, and perseverance. Its philosophy centers around self-improvement, mental focus, and peaceful resolution of conflict whenever possible.</p>
    <img src="/images/karate.jpeg" alt="Karate Class" />
  </div>

  <div class="martial-section">
    <h3>Japanese Jiujitsu (Grappling Arts)</h3>
    <p>Japanese Jiujitsu is a classical martial art from feudal Japan, originally developed by samurai to fight armed and armored opponents when weapons were not available.</p>
    <p>It focuses on joint locks, throws, pins, and defensive counters using an opponent's energy and force. Jiujitsu teaches practitioners how to control and neutralize threats efficiently.</p>
    <p>The philosophy of Jiujitsu emphasizes adaptability, strategy, and maintaining calm under pressure. It cultivates both mental flexibility and physical resilience.</p>
    <img src="/images/jiujitsu.jpeg" alt="Japanese Jiujitsu" />
  </div>

  <div class="martial-section">
    <h3>Shorinji Kempo (Striking Arts)</h3>
    <p>Shorinji Kempo was founded in Japan in 1947 by Doshin So, combining elements of Shaolin Kung Fu with Japanese martial traditions. It is a modern system of both self-defense and character development.</p>
    <p>Techniques include strikes, joint locks, throws, and pressure point applications. It is taught as both a physical discipline and a philosophical study.</p>
    <p>Its core philosophy centers on mutual respect, cooperation, and building a peaceful society through strong individuals. The motto is: "Half for one's own happiness, and half for the happiness of others."</p>
    <img src="/images/shorinji kempo1.jpeg" alt="Shorinji Kempo" />
  </div>

  <div class="martial-section">
    <h3>Hapkido (Striking Arts)</h3>
    <p>Hapkido is a Korean martial art developed in the mid-20th century, blending traditional Korean techniques with Japanese Daito-Ryu Aiki-jujutsu and other influences.</p>
    <p>It includes kicks, joint locks, throws, pressure point strikes, and weapon training. Unlike hard-style arts, Hapkido emphasizes circular motion and redirection of force.</p>
    <p>The philosophy of Hapkido promotes harmony, non-resistance, and balance. It teaches that true strength lies in flexibility and awareness, both physically and mentally.</p>
    <img src="/images/hapkido.jpeg" alt="Hapkido Class" />
  </div>

  <div class="martial-section">
    <h3>Judo (Grappling Arts)</h3>
    <p>Judo, meaning "the gentle way", was founded in Japan by Jigoro Kano in 1882. It evolved from traditional Japanese jujutsu systems into a modern Olympic sport.</p>
    <p>It focuses on throwing techniques, pins, and submissions such as arm locks and chokes. Judokas learn to use leverage and timing rather than brute strength.</p>
    <p>Judo's philosophy encourages mutual welfare and benefit. Practitioners strive for efficient movement and continuous self-improvement through rigorous practice and humility.</p>
    <img src="/images/judo1.jpeg" alt="Judo Class" />
  </div>

  <div class="martial-section">
    <h3>Mixed Martial Arts (Striking & Grappling)</h3>
    <p>Our Mixed Martial Arts (MMA) class combines effective techniques from both striking and grappling disciplines. Students will learn how to transition smoothly between stand-up combat and ground fighting.</p>
    <p>The class incorporates elements of Karate, Hapkido, Shorinji Kempo, Judo, and Jiujitsu to provide a well-rounded self-defense system and competitive foundation.</p>
    <p>Training includes striking combos, takedowns, clinch work, submissions, and practical sparring. This class is perfect for those who want a comprehensive and modern martial arts experience.</p>
    <img src="/images/mma1.jpeg" alt="Mixed Martial Arts Class" />
  </div>

